Salesforce Summer Program – Day 1 Submission
📌 1. What problem does Salesforce solve?
Salesforce solves the problem of managing customer relationships, business operations, and sales processes efficiently in one centralized platform.
Before CRM tools like Salesforce, companies stored customer information in spreadsheets, emails, or separate software systems, which caused:
Data duplication
Poor communication between teams
Loss of customer information
Slow sales processes
Difficulty tracking customer interactions
Salesforce helps organizations by:
Storing all customer data in one place
Tracking sales, leads, and customer support
Automating workflows and tasks
Improving communication between teams
Increasing productivity and customer satisfaction
It enables businesses to make better decisions using real-time data and analytics.
📌 2. What is CRM?
CRM stands for Customer Relationship Management.
CRM is a technology and strategy used by companies to manage interactions with customers and potential customers.
The main goals of CRM are:
Improving customer relationships
Increasing sales
Providing better customer support
Organizing customer data efficiently
A CRM system stores information such as:
Customer names and contact details
Purchase history
Emails and communication records
Customer issues and support tickets
Sales opportunities
Salesforce is one of the most popular cloud-based CRM platforms in the world.
📌 3. What is an Object in Salesforce? Give one example.
In Salesforce, an Object is like a database table used to store specific types of information.
Objects contain:
Fields (columns)
Records (rows/data)
Example:
The Student Object can store:
Student Name
Roll Number
Branch
Email
Phone Number
Standard Objects in Salesforce:
Lead
Contact
Account
Opportunity
Custom Objects:
Objects created by users according to business needs.
Example:
Library Management
College Attendance
Hostel Management
Objects help organize and manage data efficiently inside Salesforce.
